vlanSflspGeneralSwitchID.name: vlanSflspGeneralSwitchID
vlanSflspGeneralSwitchID.description: A 10 byte octet string uniquely identifying the switch in the Switch Fabric. By convention, to ensure uniqueness the first six bytes should default to the base mac address and the last four bytes should default to zeroes.

vlanSflspGeneralAdminStatus.name: vlanSflspGeneralAdminStatus
vlanSflspGeneralAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the SFLSP in the switch. The value 'enabled' denotes that the SFLSP Process is active on at least one interface; 'disabled' disables it on all interfaces.

vlanSflspGeneralVersion.name: vlanSflspGeneralVersion
vlanSflspGeneralVersion.description: The current version number of the SFLSP protocol is 2

vlanSflspGeneralAreaBRStatus.name: vlanSflspGeneralAreaBRStatus
vlanSflspGeneralAreaBRStatus.description: A flag to note whether this switch is an area border switch

vlanSflspGeneralASBRStatus.name: vlanSflspGeneralASBRStatus
vlanSflspGeneralASBRStatus.description: A flag to note whether this switch is an Autonomous System border switch.

vlanSflspGeneralTOSSupport.name: vlanSflspGeneralTOSSupport
vlanSflspGeneralTOSSupport.description: The switch's support for type-of-service switching. Currently, this is set to false, indicating no type-of-service switching.

vlanSflspGeneralOrgNewLSAs.name: vlanSflspGeneralOrgNewLSAs
vlanSflspGeneralOrgNewLSAs.description: Number of new link-state advertisements that have been originated. This number is incremented each time the switch originates a new LSA.

vlanSflspGeneralRcvNewLSAs.name: vlanSflspGeneralRcvNewLSAs
vlanSflspGeneralRcvNewLSAs.description: The number of link-state advertisements received determined to be new. instantiations. This number does not include newer instantiations of self-originated link-state advertisements.

vlanSflspGeneralMaxOnQueue.name: vlanSflspGeneralMaxOnQueue
vlanSflspGeneralMaxOnQueue.description: Maximum number of events on the queue

vlanSflspGeneralCurOnQueue.name: vlanSflspGeneralCurOnQueue
vlanSflspGeneralCurOnQueue.description: Current number of events on the queue

vlanSflspGeneralMaxTimeUs.name: vlanSflspGeneralMaxTimeUs
vlanSflspGeneralMaxTimeUs.description: Maximum length of time to process events on the queue

vlanSflspGeneralCurTimeUs.name: vlanSflspGeneralCurTimeUs
vlanSflspGeneralCurTimeUs.description: Current length of time to process events on the queue

vlanSflspGeneralMaxEvents.name: vlanSflspGeneralMaxEvents
vlanSflspGeneralMaxEvents.description: Maximum number of events processed at once

vlanSflspGeneralMaxTimeOccurred.name: vlanSflspGeneralMaxTimeOccurred
vlanSflspGeneralMaxTimeOccurred.description: Maximum length of time occurred at this time

vlanSflspGeneralMaxOnQOccurred.name: vlanSflspGeneralMaxOnQOccurred
vlanSflspGeneralMaxOnQOccurred.description: Maximum number of events on the queue occurred at this time

vlanSflspGeneralTotalSwLinks.name: vlanSflspGeneralTotalSwLinks
vlanSflspGeneralTotalSwLinks.description: Total number of switch links in our database

vlanSflspGeneralLastChangeDet.name: vlanSflspGeneralLastChangeDet
vlanSflspGeneralLastChangeDet.description: Timestamp of last run of spf due to change detected in topology

vlanSflspLsdbTable.name: vlanSflspLsdbTable
vlanSflspLsdbTable.description: The SFLSP Process's Links State Database.

vlanSflspLsdbAreaID.name: vlanSflspLsdbAreaID
vlanSflspLsdbAreaID.description: The 32-bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.

vlanSflspLsdbType.name: vlanSflspLsdbType
vlanSflspLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a seperate advertisement format.

vlanSflspLsdbLSID.name: vlanSflspLsdbLSID
vlanSflspLsdbLSID.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a switch ID or a switch port name; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

vlanSflspLsdbSwitchID.name: vlanSflspLsdbSwitchID
vlanSflspLsdbSwitchID.description: A 10 byte octet string uniquely identifying the orignating switch in the Switch Fabric. By convention, to ensure uniqueness the first six bytes should default to the base mac address and the last four bytes should default to zeroes.

vlanSflspLsdbSequence.name: vlanSflspLsdbSequence
vlanSflspLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence numbers the more recent the advertisement.

vlanSflspLsdbAge.name: vlanSflspLsdbAge
vlanSflspLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds .

vlanSflspLsdbChecksum.name: vlanSflspLsdbChecksum
vlanSflspLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating th checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

vlanSflspLsdbAdvertisement.name: vlanSflspLsdbAdvertisement
vlanSflspLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

vlanSflspInterfacesTable.name: vlanSflspInterfacesTable
vlanSflspInterfacesTable.description: The SFLSP Interface Table describes the interfaces from the viewpoint of SFLSP.

vlanSflspInterfacesEntry.name: vlanSflspInterfacesEntry
vlanSflspInterfacesEntry.description: The SFLSP Interfaces Entry describes one interface from the viewpoint of SFLSP

vlanSflspInterfacesIFAddress.name: vlanSflspInterfacesIFAddress
vlanSflspInterfacesIFAddress.description: A 10 byte octet string uniquely identifying the port address. By convention, to ensure uniqueness the first six bytes should default to the base mac address and the last four bytes should default to the port number of the interface.

vlanSflspInterfacesSwAddressLess.name: vlanSflspInterfacesSwAddressLess
vlanSflspInterfacesSwAddressLess.description: For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the corresponding value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.

vlanSflspInterfacesAreaID.name: vlanSflspInterfacesAreaID
vlanSflspInterfacesAreaID.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the SFLSP backbone.

vlanSflspInterfacesIfType.name: vlanSflspInterfacesIfType
vlanSflspInterfacesIfType.description: The SFLSP interface type. Currently all interfaces are handled as broadcast type.

vlanSflspInterfacesAdminStatus.name: vlanSflspInterfacesAdminStatus
vlanSflspInterfacesAdminStatus.description: The SFLSP interface's administrative status. The value 'enabled' denotes that neighbor relationships may be formed on the interface, and the interface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to SFLSP.

vlanSflspInterfacesSwPriority.name: vlanSflspInterfacesSwPriority
vlanSflspInterfacesSwPriority.description: The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated switch election algorithm. By default all switches are eligible with a priority of 1.

vlanSflspInterfacesTransDelay.name: vlanSflspInterfacesTransDelay
vlanSflspInterfacesTransDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link-state update packet over this interface.

vlanSflspInterfacesReTransInterval.name: vlanSflspInterfacesReTransInterval
vlanSflspInterfacesReTransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when re- transmitting database description and link-state request packets.

vlanSflspInterfacesHelloInterval.name: vlanSflspInterfacesHelloInterval
vlanSflspInterfacesHelloInterval.description: The lenght of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the switch sends on the interface. This value must be the same for all switches attached to a common network.

vlanSflspInterfacesDeadInterval.name: vlanSflspInterfacesDeadInterval
vlanSflspInterfacesDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a switch's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neighbors declare the switch down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all switches attached to a common network.

vlanSflspInterfacesPollInterval.name: vlanSflspInterfacesPollInterval
vlanSflspInterfacesPollInterval.description: The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive non-broadcast multi-access neighbor.

vlanSflspInterfacesDS.name: vlanSflspInterfacesDS
vlanSflspInterfacesDS.description: An octet string uniquely identifying the designated switch in the Switch Fabric. By convention, to ensure uniqueness this should default to the base mac address.

vlanSflspInterfacesBDS.name: vlanSflspInterfacesBDS
vlanSflspInterfacesBDS.description: An octet string uniquely identifying the backup designated switch in the Switch Fabric. By convention, to ensure uniqueness this should default to the base mac address.

vlanSflspInterfacesEvents.name: vlanSflspInterfacesEvents
vlanSflspInterfacesEvents.description: The number of times this SFLSP interface has changed its state, or an error has occured.

vlanSflspInterfacesAuthKey.name: vlanSflspInterfacesAuthKey
vlanSflspInterfacesAuthKey.description: THe Authentification Key. If the Area's Authorization Type is simplePassword, and the key length is shorter than 8 octets, the agent will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets.

vlanSflspIfMetricTable.name: vlanSflspIfMetricTable
vlanSflspIfMetricTable.description: The TOS metrics for a non-virtual interface indentified by the interface index.

vlanSflspIfMetricEntry.name: vlanSflspIfMetricEntry
vlanSflspIfMetricEntry.description: A particular TOS metric for a non-virtual interface identified by the interface index.

vlanSflspIfMetricIfAddress.name: vlanSflspIfMetricIfAddress
vlanSflspIfMetricIfAddress.description: A 10 byte octet string uniquely identifying the port address. By convention, to ensure uniqueness the first six bytes should default to the base mac address and the last four bytes should default to the port number of the interface.

vlanSflspIfMetricIfTOSType.name: vlanSflspIfMetricIfTOSType
vlanSflspIfMetricIfTOSType.description: The type of service metric being referenced. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance..

vlanSflspIfMetricIfMetric.name: vlanSflspIfMetricIfMetric
vlanSflspIfMetricIfMetric.description: The metric of using this type of service on this interface. The default value of the TOS 0 Metric is 10^8 / ifSpeed. The value FFFF is distinguished to mean 'no route via this TOS'.

vlanSflspIfMetricIfStatus.name: vlanSflspIfMetricIfStatus
vlanSflspIfMetricIfStatus.description: This variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent

vlanSflspNeighborsTable.name: vlanSflspNeighborsTable
vlanSflspNeighborsTable.description: A table of non-virtual neighbor information .

vlanSflspNeighborsEntry.name: vlanSflspNeighborsEntry
vlanSflspNeighborsEntry.description: The information regarding a single neighbor.

vlanSflspNeighborsPortName.name: vlanSflspNeighborsPortName
vlanSflspNeighborsPortName.description: A 10 byte octet string uniquely identifying the neighbor's port address. By convention, to ensure uniqueness the first six bytes should default to the base mac address and the last four bytes should default to the port number of the neighbor's interface.

vlanSflspNeighborsSwitchID.name: vlanSflspNeighborsSwitchID
vlanSflspNeighborsSwitchID.description: An octet string uniquely identifying the neighboring switch in the Switch Fabric. By convention, to ensure uniqueness this should default to the base mac address.

vlanSflspNeighborsOptions.name: vlanSflspNeighborsOptions
vlanSflspNeighborsOptions.description: A bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field. Bit 0, if set, indicates that the area accepts and operates on external information; if zero, it is a stub area. Bit 1, if set, indicates that the system will operate on Type of Service metrics other than TOS 0. If zero, the neighbor will ignore all metrics except the TOS 0 metric .

vlanSflspNeighborsPriority.name: vlanSflspNeighborsPriority
vlanSflspNeighborsPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designated switch election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the designated switch on this particular network.

vlanSflspNeighborsState.name: vlanSflspNeighborsState
vlanSflspNeighborsState.description: The State of the relationship with this Neighbor.

vlanSflspNeighborsEvents.name: vlanSflspNeighborsEvents
vlanSflspNeighborsEvents.description: The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state, or an error has occurred.

vlanSflspNeighborsLSRetransQLen.name: vlanSflspNeighborsLSRetransQLen
vlanSflspNeighborsLSRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.

vlanSflspNeighborsHELLOsRcvd.name: vlanSflspNeighborsHELLOsRcvd
vlanSflspNeighborsHELLOsRcvd.description: The number of hello packets received from this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsDBDsRcvd.name: vlanSflspNeighborsDBDsRcvd
vlanSflspNeighborsDBDsRcvd.description: The number of database description packets received from this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsLSUsRcvd.name: vlanSflspNeighborsLSUsRcvd
vlanSflspNeighborsLSUsRcvd.description: The number of link state update packets received from this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsLSRsRcvd.name: vlanSflspNeighborsLSRsRcvd
vlanSflspNeighborsLSRsRcvd.description: The number of link state request packets received from this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsLSACKsRcvd.name: vlanSflspNeighborsLSACKsRcvd
vlanSflspNeighborsLSACKsRcvd.description: The number of link state acknowledgement packets received from this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsHELLOsSent.name: vlanSflspNeighborsHELLOsSent
vlanSflspNeighborsHELLOsSent.description: The number of hello packets sent to this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsDBDsSent.name: vlanSflspNeighborsDBDsSent
vlanSflspNeighborsDBDsSent.description: The number of database description packets sent to this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsLSUsSent.name: vlanSflspNeighborsLSUsSent
vlanSflspNeighborsLSUsSent.description: The number of link state update packets sent to this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsLSRsSent.name: vlanSflspNeighborsLSRsSent
vlanSflspNeighborsLSRsSent.description: The number of link state request packets sent to this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsLSACKsSent.name: vlanSflspNeighborsLSACKsSent
vlanSflspNeighborsLSACKsSent.description: The number of link state acknowledgement packets sent to this neighbor

vlanSflspNeighborsNBMAStatus.name: vlanSflspNeighborsNBMAStatus
vlanSflspNeighborsNBMAStatus.description: The variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependant.

vlanSflspNeighborsFULLTimeSec.name: vlanSflspNeighborsFULLTimeSec
vlanSflspNeighborsFULLTimeSec.description: Neighbor went to FULL state at this time

vlanSflspAreaTable.name: vlanSflspAreaTable
vlanSflspAreaTable.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of the switches attached areas.

vlanSflspAreaEntry.name: vlanSflspAreaEntry
vlanSflspAreaEntry.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of one of the switches attached areas.

vlanSflspAreaAreaID.name: vlanSflspAreaAreaID
vlanSflspAreaAreaID.description: A 10 byte octet string uniquely identifying an area.

vlanSflspAreaAuthType.name: vlanSflspAreaAuthType
vlanSflspAreaAuthType.description: The authentication type specified for an area. Additional authentication types may be assigned locally on a per Area basis.

vlanSflspAreaSPFRuns.name: vlanSflspAreaSPFRuns
vlanSflspAreaSPFRuns.description: The number of times that the intra-area route table has been calculated using this area's link-state database. This is typically done using Dijkstra's algorithm.

vlanSflspAreaABRCount.name: vlanSflspAreaABRCount
vlanSflspAreaABRCount.description: The total number of area border switches reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF Pass.

vlanSflspAreaASBRCount.name: vlanSflspAreaASBRCount
vlanSflspAreaASBRCount.description: The total number of Autonomous System border switches reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each LSP Pass.

vlanSflspAreaAreaLSACnt.name: vlanSflspAreaAreaLSACnt
vlanSflspAreaAreaLSACnt.description: The total number of link-state advertisements in this area's link-state database, excluding AS External LSA's

vlanSflspAreaAreaCheckSum.name: vlanSflspAreaAreaCheckSum
vlanSflspAreaAreaCheckSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this area's link-state database. This sum excludes external (LS type 5) link-state advertisements. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a switches link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two switches.

vlanSflspAreaLastSpfRun.name: vlanSflspAreaLastSpfRun
vlanSflspAreaLastSpfRun.description: Timestamp of last run of spf

vlanSflsp1stHopTable.name: vlanSflsp1stHopTable
vlanSflsp1stHopTable.description: This table contains the SecureFast path next-hop table. It reports various information about the next switch port address on the path to a particular destination switch port address.

vlanSflsp1stHopEntry.name: vlanSflsp1stHopEntry
vlanSflsp1stHopEntry.description: Each entry describes the next hop switch port addresses for each destination switch port address.

vlanSflsp1stHopDestSwitch.name: vlanSflsp1stHopDestSwitch
vlanSflsp1stHopDestSwitch.description: This is the index to the table, representing destination switch port addresses for each port address within the switch fabric.

vlanSflsp1stHopPath11stHop.name: vlanSflsp1stHopPath11stHop
vlanSflsp1stHopPath11stHop.description: The 1st hop of the 1st path to the destination switch

vlanSflsp1stHopPath21stHop.name: vlanSflsp1stHopPath21stHop
vlanSflsp1stHopPath21stHop.description: The 1st host of the 2nd path to the destination switch

vlanSflsp1stHopPath31stHop.name: vlanSflsp1stHopPath31stHop
vlanSflsp1stHopPath31stHop.description: The 1st hop of the 3rd path to the destination switch

vlanSflspTracePathAPIDest.name: vlanSflspTracePathAPIDest
vlanSflspTracePathAPIDest.description: This is the switch address for which a path list will be requested in the sfTracePathTable.

vlanSflspTracePathAPIID.name: vlanSflspTracePathAPIID
vlanSflspTracePathAPIID.description: This is an ID to uniquely identify the path list request in the sfTracePathTable.

vlanSflspTracePathAPIType.name: vlanSflspTracePathAPIType
vlanSflspTracePathAPIType.description: The administrative control of the trace path request entry in the sfTracePathTable. It is used to create or delete a trace path request entry.

vlanSflspTracePathAPIAction.name: vlanSflspTracePathAPIAction
vlanSflspTracePathAPIAction.description: The action to be performed by the trace path request entry in the sfTracePathTable.

vlanSflspTracePathTable.name: vlanSflspTracePathTable
vlanSflspTracePathTable.description: This table allows the determination of paths to known destinations using the same internal methods used by the switch to program these paths. It is indexed by destination switch address and a request identifier. If successful, the resulting path, which consists of a list of switch port addresses, is reported in the sfTracePathReqHopTable.

vlanSflspTracePathEntry.name: vlanSflspTracePathEntry
vlanSflspTracePathEntry.description: An SF Trace Path Table entry containing objects for a particular destination switch.

vlanSflspTracePathDest.name: vlanSflspTracePathDest
vlanSflspTracePathDest.description: The switch address of the requested destination.

vlanSflspTracePathID.name: vlanSflspTracePathID
vlanSflspTracePathID.description: A unique identifier for this path request.

vlanSflspTracePathAction.name: vlanSflspTracePathAction
vlanSflspTracePathAction.description: The action to be performed by this trace path entry.

vlanSflspTracePathStatus.name: vlanSflspTracePathStatus
vlanSflspTracePathStatus.description: The results of a trace path request. A result of success(4) means the device has determined at least one path to the destination.

vlanSflspTracePathListTable.name: vlanSflspTracePathListTable
vlanSflspTracePathListTable.description: This table contains the SecureFast Trace Path List table.

vlanSflspTracePathListEntry.name: vlanSflspTracePathListEntry
vlanSflspTracePathListEntry.description: This table contains the switch port addresses of each hop of each path traversed for a particular destination switch. These paths correspond to trace path requests in the sfTracePathReqTable.

vlanSflspTracePathListDest.name: vlanSflspTracePathListDest
vlanSflspTracePathListDest.description: The switch address of the destination for this trace path entry, corresponding to a requested destination in the sfTracePathReqTable.

vlanSflspTracePathListID.name: vlanSflspTracePathListID
vlanSflspTracePathListID.description: A unique identifier corresponding to the identifier in a trace path request in the sfTracePathReqTable.

vlanSflspTracePathListPathNum.name: vlanSflspTracePathListPathNum
vlanSflspTracePathListPathNum.description: The number of this path in the table of networks traversed. This value represents a unique path id when there are multiple paths to a single destination.

vlanSflspTracePathListHopNum.name: vlanSflspTracePathListHopNum
vlanSflspTracePathListHopNum.description: The hop number in this path.

vlanSflspTracePathListHopAddr.name: vlanSflspTracePathListHopAddr
vlanSflspTracePathListHopAddr.description: The switch port address of this hop on the path.
